cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.DC

The paper discusses a method of covertly leaking data from secure or air-gapped networks via networking equipment such as LAN switches and routers. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the technical background of switches and routers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the method, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
